This renovated shop promotes ordering by touch screen at dual kiosks. Ordering is fairly simple and quick, but it can take a minute or two to find menu items as you scroll through the categories (Sandwiches, Salads,  Sides, McCafé, etc.). After paying (by credit card, for me), you take your receipt (or order number placard if eating in) to the pick up area and wait for your number to be called. If eating in, a server brings the food to your table. Since the reopened shop and ordering kiosks are still new to the neighborhood, some people entering the shop get in what they think is the line to order, but it's people waiting for their orders. A server will still take orders at a cash register if you don't or can't use the kiosk. Some days, it's fast; others, not so much. But it's okay with me. 👍🏻
